cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI

The paper deals with the analysis of information flow between subsystems of a complex network, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The use of Granger causality and multivariate time series data suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the application of the proposed approach to resting state functional magnetic resonance imaging data implies a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study of redundancy and synergy in complex systems suggests a possible link to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
